The paper discusses the efficient search across peer databases in P2P systems, which involves data management and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of clustering and hypergraphs, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
